45void LzmaEncProps_Init(CLzmaEncProps *p)
46{
47 p->level = 5;
48 p->dictSize = p->mc = 0;
49 p->lc = p->lp = p->pb = p->algo = p->fb = p->btMode = p->numHashBytes = p->numThreads = -1;
50 p->writeEndMark = 0;
51}
52
53void LzmaEncProps_Normalize(CLzmaEncProps *p)
54{
55 int level = p->level;
56 if (level < 0)
57 level = 5;
58 p->level = level;
59 if (p->dictSize == 0)
60 p->dictSize = (level <= 5 ? (1 << (level * 2 + 14)) : (level == 6 ? (1 << 25) : (1 << 26)));
61 if (p->lc < 0)
62 p->lc = 3;
63 if (p->lp < 0)
64 p->lp = 0;
65 if (p->pb < 0)
66 p->pb = 2;
67 if (p->algo < 0)
68 p->algo = (level < 5 ? 0 : 1);
69 if (p->fb < 0)
70 p->fb = (level < 7 ? 32 : 64);
71 if (p->btMode < 0)
72 p->btMode = (p->algo == 0 ? 0 : 1);
73 if (p->numHashBytes < 0)
74 p->numHashBytes = 4;
75 if (p->mc == 0)
76 p->mc = (16 + (p->fb >> 1)) >> (p->btMode ? 0 : 1);
77 if (p->numThreads < 0)
78 p->numThreads =
79#ifndef _7ZIP_ST
80 ((p->btMode && p->algo) ? 2 : 1);
81#else
82 1;
83#endif
84}

116void LzmaEnc_FastPosInit(Byte *g_FastPos)
117{
118 int c = 2, slotFast;
119 g_FastPos[0] = 0;
120 g_FastPos[1] = 1;
121
122 for (slotFast = 2; slotFast < kNumLogBits * 2; slotFast++)
123 {
124 UInt32 k = (1 << ((slotFast >> 1) - 1));
125 UInt32 j;
126 for (j = 0; j < k; j++, c++)
127 g_FastPos[c] = (Byte) slotFast;
128 }
129}

131#define BSR2_RET(pos, res) { UInt32 i = 6 + ((kNumLogBits - 1) & \
132 (0 - (((((UInt32)1 << (kNumLogBits + 6)) - 1) - pos) >> 31))); \
133 res = p->g_FastPos[pos >> i] + (i * 2); }
134/*

136 p->g_FastPos[pos >> 6] + 12 : \
137 p->g_FastPos[pos >> (6 + kNumLogBits - 1)] + (6 + (kNumLogBits - 1)) * 2; }
138 */

340void LzmaEnc_SaveState(CLzmaEncHandle pp)
341{
342 CLzmaEnc *p = (CLzmaEnc *) pp;
343 CSaveState *dest = &p->saveState;
344 int i;
345 dest->lenEnc = p->lenEnc;
346 dest->repLenEnc = p->repLenEnc;
347 dest->state = p->state;
348
349 for (i = 0; i < kNumStates; i++)
350 {
351 memcpy(dest->isMatch[i], p->isMatch[i], sizeof(p->isMatch[i]));
352 memcpy(dest->isRep0Long[i], p->isRep0Long[i], sizeof(p->isRep0Long[i]));
353 }
354 for (i = 0; i < kNumLenToPosStates; i++)
355 memcpy(dest->posSlotEncoder[i], p->posSlotEncoder[i], sizeof(p->posSlotEncoder[i]));
356 memcpy(dest->isRep, p->isRep, sizeof(p->isRep));
357 memcpy(dest->isRepG0, p->isRepG0, sizeof(p->isRepG0));
358 memcpy(dest->isRepG1, p->isRepG1, sizeof(p->isRepG1));
359 memcpy(dest->isRepG2, p->isRepG2, sizeof(p->isRepG2));
360 memcpy(dest->posEncoders, p->posEncoders, sizeof(p->posEncoders));
361 memcpy(dest->posAlignEncoder, p->posAlignEncoder, sizeof(p->posAlignEncoder));
362 memcpy(dest->reps, p->reps, sizeof(p->reps));
363 memcpy(dest->litProbs, p->litProbs, (0x300 << p->lclp) * sizeof(CLzmaProb));
364}

392SRes LzmaEnc_SetProps(CLzmaEncHandle pp, const CLzmaEncProps *props2)
393{
394 CLzmaEnc *p = (CLzmaEnc *) pp;
395 CLzmaEncProps props = *props2;
396 LzmaEncProps_Normalize(&props);
397
398 if (props.lc > LZMA_LC_MAX || props.lp > LZMA_LP_MAX || props.pb > LZMA_PB_MAX || props.dictSize > ((UInt32) 1
399 << kDicLogSizeMaxCompress) || props.dictSize > ((UInt32) 1 << 30))
400 return SZ_ERROR_PARAM;
401 p->dictSize = props.dictSize;
402 p->matchFinderCycles = props.mc;
403 {
404 unsigned fb = props.fb;
405 if (fb < 5)
406 fb = 5;
407 if (fb > LZMA_MATCH_LEN_MAX)
408 fb = LZMA_MATCH_LEN_MAX;
409 p->numFastBytes = fb;
410 }
411 p->lc = props.lc;
412 p->lp = props.lp;
413 p->pb = props.pb;
414 p->fastMode = (props.algo == 0);
415 p->matchFinderBase.btMode = props.btMode;
416 {
417 UInt32 numHashBytes = 4;
418 if (props.btMode)
419 {
420 if (props.numHashBytes < 2)
421 numHashBytes = 2;
422 else if (props.numHashBytes < 4)
423 numHashBytes = props.numHashBytes;
424 }
425 p->matchFinderBase.numHashBytes = numHashBytes;
426 }
427
428 p->matchFinderBase.cutValue = props.mc;
429
430 p->writeEndMark = props.writeEndMark;
431
432#ifndef _7ZIP_ST
433 /*
434 if (newMultiThread != _multiThread)
435 {
436 ReleaseMatchFinder();
437 _multiThread = newMultiThread;
438 }
439 */
440 p->multiThread = (props.numThreads > 1);
441#endif
442
443 return SZ_OK;
444}

498static void RangeEnc_FlushStream(CRangeEnc *p)
499{
500 size_t num;
501 if (p->res != SZ_OK)
502 return;
503 num = p->buf - p->bufBase;
504 if (num != p->outStream->Write(p->outStream, p->bufBase, num))
505 p->res = SZ_ERROR_WRITE;
506 p->processed += num;
507 p->buf = p->bufBase;
508}

510static void MY_FAST_CALL RangeEnc_ShiftLow(CRangeEnc *p)
511{
512 if ((UInt32) p->low < (UInt32) 0xFF000000 || (int) (p->low >> 32) != 0)
513 {
514 Byte temp = p->cache;
515 do
516 {
517 Byte *buf = p->buf;
518 *buf++ = (Byte) (temp + (Byte) (p->low >> 32));
519 p->buf = buf;
520 if (buf == p->bufLim)
521 RangeEnc_FlushStream(p);
522 temp = 0xFF;
523 } while (--p->cacheSize != 0);
524 p->cache = (Byte) ((UInt32) p->low >> 24);
525 }
526 p->cacheSize++;
527 p->low = (UInt32) p->low << 8;
528}

530static void RangeEnc_FlushData(CRangeEnc *p)
531{
532 int i;
533 for (i = 0; i < 5; i++)
534 RangeEnc_ShiftLow(p);
535}

537static void RangeEnc_EncodeDirectBits(CRangeEnc *p, UInt32 value, int numBits)
538{
539 do
540 {
541 p->range >>= 1;
542 p->low += p->range & (0 - ((value >> --numBits) & 1));
543 if (p->range < kTopValue)
544 {
545 p->range <<= 8;
546 RangeEnc_ShiftLow(p);
547 }
548 } while (numBits != 0);
549}
550
551static void RangeEnc_EncodeBit(CRangeEnc *p, CLzmaProb *prob, UInt32 symbol)
552{
553 UInt32 ttt = *prob;
554 UInt32 newBound = (p->range >> kNumBitModelTotalBits) * ttt;
555 if (symbol == 0)
556 {
557 p->range = newBound;
558 ttt += (kBitModelTotal - ttt) >> kNumMoveBits;
559 }
560 else
561 {
562 p->low += newBound;
563 p->range -= newBound;
564 ttt -= ttt >> kNumMoveBits;
565 }
566 *prob = (CLzmaProb) ttt;
567 if (p->range < kTopValue)
568 {
569 p->range <<= 8;
570 RangeEnc_ShiftLow(p);
571 }
572}

574static void LitEnc_Encode(CRangeEnc *p, CLzmaProb *probs, UInt32 symbol)
575{
576 symbol |= 0x100;
577 do
578 {
579 RangeEnc_EncodeBit(p, probs + (symbol >> 8), (symbol >> 7) & 1);
580 symbol <<= 1;
581 } while (symbol < 0x10000);
582}
583
584static void LitEnc_EncodeMatched(CRangeEnc *p, CLzmaProb *probs, UInt32 symbol, UInt32 matchByte)
585{
586 UInt32 offs = 0x100;
587 symbol |= 0x100;
588 do
589 {
590 matchByte <<= 1;
591 RangeEnc_EncodeBit(p, probs + (offs + (matchByte & offs) + (symbol >> 8)), (symbol >> 7) & 1);
592 symbol <<= 1;
593 offs &= ~(matchByte ^ symbol);
594 } while (symbol < 0x10000);
595}

597void LzmaEnc_InitPriceTables(UInt32 *ProbPrices)
598{
599 UInt32 i;
600 for (i = (1 << kNumMoveReducingBits) / 2; i < kBitModelTotal; i += (1 << kNumMoveReducingBits))
601 {
602 const int kCyclesBits = kNumBitPriceShiftBits;
603 UInt32 w = i;
604 UInt32 bitCount = 0;
605 int j;
606 for (j = 0; j < kCyclesBits; j++)
607 {
608 w = w * w;
609 bitCount <<= 1;
610 while (w >= ((UInt32) 1 << 16))
611 {
612 w >>= 1;
613 bitCount++;
614 }
615 }
616 ProbPrices[i >> kNumMoveReducingBits] = ((kNumBitModelTotalBits << kCyclesBits) - 15 - bitCount);
617 }
618}

620#define GET_PRICE(prob, symbol) \
621 p->ProbPrices[((prob) ^ (((-(int)(symbol))) & (kBitModelTotal - 1))) >> kNumMoveReducingBits];
622
623#define GET_PRICEa(prob, symbol) \
624 ProbPrices[((prob) ^ ((-((int)(symbol))) & (kBitModelTotal - 1))) >> kNumMoveReducingBits];
625
626#define GET_PRICE_0(prob) p->ProbPrices[(prob) >> kNumMoveReducingBits]
627#define GET_PRICE_1(prob) p->ProbPrices[((prob) ^ (kBitModelTotal - 1)) >> kNumMoveReducingBits]
628
629#define GET_PRICE_0a(prob) ProbPrices[(prob) >> kNumMoveReducingBits]
630#define GET_PRICE_1a(prob) ProbPrices[((prob) ^ (kBitModelTotal - 1)) >> kNumMoveReducingBits]

632static UInt32 LitEnc_GetPrice(const CLzmaProb *probs, UInt32 symbol, UInt32 *ProbPrices)
633{
634 UInt32 price = 0;
635 symbol |= 0x100;
636 do
637 {
638 price += GET_PRICEa(probs[symbol >> 8], (symbol >> 7) & 1);
639 symbol <<= 1;
640 } while (symbol < 0x10000);
641 return price;
642}

644static UInt32 LitEnc_GetPriceMatched(const CLzmaProb *probs, UInt32 symbol, UInt32 matchByte, UInt32 *ProbPrices)
645{
646 UInt32 price = 0;
647 UInt32 offs = 0x100;
648 symbol |= 0x100;
649 do
650 {
651 matchByte <<= 1;
652 price += GET_PRICEa(probs[offs + (matchByte & offs) + (symbol >> 8)], (symbol >> 7) & 1);
653 symbol <<= 1;
654 offs &= ~(matchByte ^ symbol);
655 } while (symbol < 0x10000);
656 return price;
657}

659static void RcTree_Encode(CRangeEnc *rc, CLzmaProb *probs, int numBitLevels, UInt32 symbol)
660{
661 UInt32 m = 1;
662 int i;
663 for (i = numBitLevels; i != 0;)
664 {
665 UInt32 bit;
666 i--;
667 bit = (symbol >> i) & 1;
668 RangeEnc_EncodeBit(rc, probs + m, bit);
669 m = (m << 1) | bit;
670 }
671}
672
673static void RcTree_ReverseEncode(CRangeEnc *rc, CLzmaProb *probs, int numBitLevels, UInt32 symbol)
674{
675 UInt32 m = 1;
676 int i;
677 for (i = 0; i < numBitLevels; i++)
678 {
679 UInt32 bit = symbol & 1;
680 RangeEnc_EncodeBit(rc, probs + m, bit);
681 m = (m << 1) | bit;
682 symbol >>= 1;
683 }
684}

686static UInt32 RcTree_GetPrice(const CLzmaProb *probs, int numBitLevels, UInt32 symbol, UInt32 *ProbPrices)
687{
688 UInt32 price = 0;
689 symbol |= (1 << numBitLevels);
690 while (symbol != 1)
691 {
692 price += GET_PRICEa(probs[symbol >> 1], symbol & 1);
693 symbol >>= 1;
694 }
695 return price;
696}
697
698static UInt32 RcTree_ReverseGetPrice(const CLzmaProb *probs, int numBitLevels, UInt32 symbol, UInt32 *ProbPrices)
699{
700 UInt32 price = 0;
701 UInt32 m = 1;
702 int i;
703 for (i = numBitLevels; i != 0; i--)
704 {
705 UInt32 bit = symbol & 1;
706 symbol >>= 1;
707 price += GET_PRICEa(probs[m], bit);
708 m = (m << 1) | bit;
709 }
710 return price;
711}

713static void LenEnc_Init(CLenEnc *p)
714{
715 unsigned i;
716 p->choice = p->choice2 = kProbInitValue;
717 for (i = 0; i < (LZMA_NUM_PB_STATES_MAX << kLenNumLowBits); i++)
718 p->low[i] = kProbInitValue;
719 for (i = 0; i < (LZMA_NUM_PB_STATES_MAX << kLenNumMidBits); i++)
720 p->mid[i] = kProbInitValue;
721 for (i = 0; i < kLenNumHighSymbols; i++)
722 p->high[i] = kProbInitValue;
723}

725static void LenEnc_Encode(CLenEnc *p, CRangeEnc *rc, UInt32 symbol, UInt32 posState)
726{
727 if (symbol < kLenNumLowSymbols)
728 {
729 RangeEnc_EncodeBit(rc, &p->choice, 0);
730 RcTree_Encode(rc, p->low + (posState << kLenNumLowBits), kLenNumLowBits, symbol);
731 }
732 else
733 {
734 RangeEnc_EncodeBit(rc, &p->choice, 1);
735 if (symbol < kLenNumLowSymbols + kLenNumMidSymbols)
736 {
737 RangeEnc_EncodeBit(rc, &p->choice2, 0);
738 RcTree_Encode(rc, p->mid + (posState << kLenNumMidBits), kLenNumMidBits, symbol - kLenNumLowSymbols);
739 }
740 else
741 {
742 RangeEnc_EncodeBit(rc, &p->choice2, 1);
743 RcTree_Encode(rc, p->high, kLenNumHighBits, symbol - kLenNumLowSymbols - kLenNumMidSymbols);
744 }
745 }
746}

748static void LenEnc_SetPrices(CLenEnc *p, UInt32 posState, UInt32 numSymbols, UInt32 *prices, UInt32 *ProbPrices)
749{
750 UInt32 a0 = GET_PRICE_0a(p->choice);
751 UInt32 a1 = GET_PRICE_1a(p->choice);
752 UInt32 b0 = a1 + GET_PRICE_0a(p->choice2);
753 UInt32 b1 = a1 + GET_PRICE_1a(p->choice2);
754 UInt32 i = 0;
755 for (i = 0; i < kLenNumLowSymbols; i++)
756 {
757 if (i >= numSymbols)
758 return;
759 prices[i] = a0 + RcTree_GetPrice(p->low + (posState << kLenNumLowBits), kLenNumLowBits, i, ProbPrices);
760 }
761 for (; i < kLenNumLowSymbols + kLenNumMidSymbols; i++)
762 {
763 if (i >= numSymbols)
764 return;
765 prices[i] = b0 + RcTree_GetPrice(p->mid + (posState << kLenNumMidBits), kLenNumMidBits, i - kLenNumLowSymbols, ProbPrices);
766 }
767 for (; i < numSymbols; i++)
768 prices[i] = b1 + RcTree_GetPrice(p->high, kLenNumHighBits, i - kLenNumLowSymbols - kLenNumMidSymbols, ProbPrices);
769}

877static UInt32 Backward(CLzmaEnc *p, UInt32 *backRes, UInt32 cur)
878{
879 UInt32 posMem = p->opt[cur].posPrev;
880 UInt32 backMem = p->opt[cur].backPrev;
881 p->optimumEndIndex = cur;
882 do
883 {
884 if (p->opt[cur].prev1IsChar)
885 {
886 MakeAsChar(&p->opt[posMem])
887 p->opt[posMem].posPrev = posMem - 1;
888 if (p->opt[cur].prev2)
889 {
890 p->opt[posMem - 1].prev1IsChar = False;
891 p->opt[posMem - 1].posPrev = p->opt[cur].posPrev2;
892 p->opt[posMem - 1].backPrev = p->opt[cur].backPrev2;
893 }
894 }
895 {
896 UInt32 posPrev = posMem;
897 UInt32 backCur = backMem;
898
899 backMem = p->opt[posPrev].backPrev;
900 posMem = p->opt[posPrev].posPrev;
901
902 p->opt[posPrev].backPrev = backCur;
903 p->opt[posPrev].posPrev = cur;
904 cur = posPrev;
905 }
906 } while (cur != 0);
907 *backRes = p->opt[0].backPrev;
908 p->optimumCurrentIndex = p->opt[0].posPrev;
909 return p->optimumCurrentIndex;
910}

1326 if (limit > numAvailFull)

1328 for (; lenTest2 < limit && data[lenTest2] == data2[lenTest2]; lenTest2++)
1329 ;
1330 lenTest2 -= lenTest + 1;
1331 if (lenTest2 >= 2)
1332 {
1333 UInt32 state2 = kRepNextStates[state];
1334 UInt32 posStateNext = (position + lenTest) & p->pbMask;
1335 UInt32 curAndLenCharPrice = price + p->repLenEnc.prices[posState][lenTest - 2]
1336 + GET_PRICE_0(p->isMatch[state2][posStateNext]) + LitEnc_GetPriceMatched(
1337 LIT_PROBS(position + lenTest, data[lenTest - 1]), data[lenTest], data2[lenTest], p->ProbPrices);
1338 state2 = kLiteralNextStates[state2];
1339 posStateNext = (position + lenTest + 1) & p->pbMask;
1340 nextRepMatchPrice = curAndLenCharPrice + GET_PRICE_1(p->isMatch[state2][posStateNext])
1341 + GET_PRICE_1(p->isRep[state2]);
1342
1343 /* for (; lenTest2 >= 2; lenTest2--) */
1344 {
1345 UInt32 curAndLenPrice;
1346 COptimal *opt;
1347 UInt32 offset = cur + lenTest + 1 + lenTest2;
1348 while (lenEnd < offset)
1349 p->opt[++lenEnd].price = kInfinityPrice;
1350 curAndLenPrice = nextRepMatchPrice + GetRepPrice(p, 0, lenTest2, state2, posStateNext);
1351 opt = &p->opt[offset];
1352 if (curAndLenPrice < opt->price)
1353 {
1354 opt->price = curAndLenPrice;
1355 opt->posPrev = cur + lenTest + 1;
1356 opt->backPrev = 0;
1357 opt->prev1IsChar = True;
1358 opt->prev2 = True;
1359 opt->posPrev2 = cur;
1360 opt->backPrev2 = repIndex;
1361 }
1362 }
1363 }
1364 }
1365 }
1366 }
1367 /* for (UInt32 lenTest = 2; lenTest <= newLen; lenTest++) */
1368 if (newLen > numAvail)
1369 {
1370 newLen = numAvail;
1371 for (numPairs = 0; newLen > matches[numPairs]; numPairs += 2)
1372 ;
1373 matches[numPairs] = newLen;
1374 numPairs += 2;
1375 }
1376 if (newLen >= startLen)
1377 {
1378 UInt32 normalMatchPrice = matchPrice + GET_PRICE_0(p->isRep[state]);
1379 UInt32 offs, curBack, posSlot;
1380 UInt32 lenTest;
1381 while (lenEnd < cur + newLen)
1382 p->opt[++lenEnd].price = kInfinityPrice;
1383
1384 offs = 0;
1385 while (startLen > matches[offs])
1386 offs += 2;
1387 curBack = matches[offs + 1];
1388 GetPosSlot2(curBack, posSlot);
1389 for (lenTest = /*2*/startLen;; lenTest++)
1390 {
1391 UInt32 curAndLenPrice = normalMatchPrice + p->lenEnc.prices[posState][lenTest - LZMA_MATCH_LEN_MIN];
1392 UInt32 lenToPosState = GetLenToPosState(lenTest);
1393 COptimal *opt;
1394 if (curBack < kNumFullDistances)
1395 curAndLenPrice += p->distancesPrices[lenToPosState][curBack];
1396 else
1397 curAndLenPrice += p->posSlotPrices[lenToPosState][posSlot] + p->alignPrices[curBack & kAlignMask];
1398
1399 opt = &p->opt[cur + lenTest];
1400 if (curAndLenPrice < opt->price)
1401 {
1402 opt->price = curAndLenPrice;
1403 opt->posPrev = cur;
1404 opt->backPrev = curBack + LZMA_NUM_REPS;
1405 opt->prev1IsChar = False;
1406 }
1407
1408 if (/*_maxMode && */lenTest == matches[offs])
1409 {
1410 /* Try Match + Literal + Rep0 */
1411 const Byte *data2 = data - (curBack + 1);
1412 UInt32 lenTest2 = lenTest + 1;
1413 UInt32 limit = lenTest2 + p->numFastBytes;
1414 UInt32 nextRepMatchPrice;
1415 if (limit > numAvailFull)
1416 limit = numAvailFull;
1417 for (; lenTest2 < limit && data[lenTest2] == data2[lenTest2]; lenTest2++)
1418 ;
1419 lenTest2 -= lenTest + 1;
1420 if (lenTest2 >= 2)
1421 {
1422 UInt32 state2 = kMatchNextStates[state];
1423 UInt32 posStateNext = (position + lenTest) & p->pbMask;
1424 UInt32 curAndLenCharPrice = curAndLenPrice + GET_PRICE_0(p->isMatch[state2][posStateNext])
1425 +
1426 LitEnc_GetPriceMatched(LIT_PROBS(position + lenTest, data[lenTest - 1]), data[lenTest], data2[lenTest],
1427 p->ProbPrices);
1428 state2 = kLiteralNextStates[state2];
1429 posStateNext = (posStateNext + 1) & p->pbMask;
1430 nextRepMatchPrice = curAndLenCharPrice + GET_PRICE_1(p->isMatch[state2][posStateNext])
1431 + GET_PRICE_1(p->isRep[state2]);
1432
1433 /* for (; lenTest2 >= 2; lenTest2--) */
1434 {
1435 UInt32 offset = cur + lenTest + 1 + lenTest2;
1436 UInt32 curAndLenPrice;
1437 COptimal *opt;
1438 while (lenEnd < offset)
1439 p->opt[++lenEnd].price = kInfinityPrice;
1440 curAndLenPrice = nextRepMatchPrice + GetRepPrice(p, 0, lenTest2, state2, posStateNext);
1441 opt = &p->opt[offset];
1442 if (curAndLenPrice < opt->price)
1443 {
1444 opt->price = curAndLenPrice;
1445 opt->posPrev = cur + lenTest + 1;
1446 opt->backPrev = 0;
1447 opt->prev1IsChar = True;
1448 opt->prev2 = True;
1449 opt->posPrev2 = cur;
1450 opt->backPrev2 = curBack + LZMA_NUM_REPS;
1451 }
1452 }
1453 }
1454 offs += 2;
1455 if (offs == numPairs)
1456 break;
1457 curBack = matches[offs + 1];
1458 if (curBack >= kNumFullDistances)
1459 GetPosSlot2(curBack, posSlot);
1460 }
1461 }
1462 }
1463 }
1464}

1466#define ChangePair(smallDist, bigDist) (((bigDist) >> 7) > (smallDist))

1468static UInt32 GetOptimumFast(CLzmaEnc *p, UInt32 *backRes)
1469{
1470 UInt32 numAvail, mainLen, mainDist, numPairs, repIndex, repLen, i;
1471 const Byte *data;
1472 const UInt32 *matches;
1473
1474 if (p->additionalOffset == 0)
1475 mainLen = ReadMatchDistances(p, &numPairs);
1476 else
1477 {
1478 mainLen = p->longestMatchLength;
1479 numPairs = p->numPairs;
1480 }
1481
1482 numAvail = p->numAvail;
1483 *backRes = (UInt32) -1;
1484 if (numAvail < 2)
1485 return 1;
1486 if (numAvail > LZMA_MATCH_LEN_MAX)
1487 numAvail = LZMA_MATCH_LEN_MAX;
1488 data = p->matchFinder.GetPointerToCurrentPos(p->matchFinderObj) - 1;
1489
1490 repLen = repIndex = 0;
1491 for (i = 0; i < LZMA_NUM_REPS; i++)
1492 {
1493 UInt32 len;
1494 const Byte *data2 = data - (p->reps[i] + 1);
1495 if (data[0] != data2[0] || data[1] != data2[1])
1496 continue;
1497 for (len = 2; len < numAvail && data[len] == data2[len]; len++)
1498 ;
1499 if (len >= p->numFastBytes)
1500 {
1501 *backRes = i;
1502 MovePos(p, len - 1);
1503 return len;
1504 }
1505 if (len > repLen)
1506 {
1507 repIndex = i;
1508 repLen = len;
1509 }
1510 }
1511
1512 matches = p->matches;
1513 if (mainLen >= p->numFastBytes)
1514 {
1515 *backRes = matches[numPairs - 1] + LZMA_NUM_REPS;
1516 MovePos(p, mainLen - 1);
1517 return mainLen;
1518 }
1519
1520 mainDist = 0; /* for GCC */
1521 if (mainLen >= 2)
1522 {
1523 mainDist = matches[numPairs - 1];
1524 while (numPairs > 2 && mainLen == matches[numPairs - 4] + 1)
1525 {
1526 if (!ChangePair(matches[numPairs - 3], mainDist))
1527 break;
1528 numPairs -= 2;
1529 mainLen = matches[numPairs - 2];
1530 mainDist = matches[numPairs - 1];
1531 }
1532 if (mainLen == 2 && mainDist >= 0x80)
1533 mainLen = 1;
1534 }
1535
1536 if (repLen >= 2 && ((repLen + 1 >= mainLen) || (repLen + 2 >= mainLen && mainDist >= (1 << 9)) || (repLen + 3 >= mainLen && mainDist
1537 >= (1 << 15))))
1538 {
1539 *backRes = repIndex;
1540 MovePos(p, repLen - 1);
1541 return repLen;
1542 }
1543
1544 if (mainLen < 2 || numAvail <= 2)
1545 return 1;
1546
1547 p->longestMatchLength = ReadMatchDistances(p, &p->numPairs);
1548 if (p->longestMatchLength >= 2)
1549 {
1550 UInt32 newDistance = matches[p->numPairs - 1];
1551 if ((p->longestMatchLength >= mainLen && newDistance < mainDist) || (p->longestMatchLength == mainLen + 1
1552 && !ChangePair(mainDist, newDistance)) || (p->longestMatchLength > mainLen + 1) || (p->longestMatchLength + 1 >= mainLen
1553 && mainLen >= 3 && ChangePair(newDistance, mainDist)))
1554 return 1;
1555 }
1556
1557 data = p->matchFinder.GetPointerToCurrentPos(p->matchFinderObj) - 1;
1558 for (i = 0; i < LZMA_NUM_REPS; i++)
1559 {
1560 UInt32 len, limit;
1561 const Byte *data2 = data - (p->reps[i] + 1);
1562 if (data[0] != data2[0] || data[1] != data2[1])
1563 continue;
1564 limit = mainLen - 1;
1565 for (len = 2; len < limit && data[len] == data2[len]; len++)
1566 ;
1567 if (len >= limit)
1568 return 1;
1569 }
1570 *backRes = mainDist + LZMA_NUM_REPS;
1571 MovePos(p, mainLen - 2);
1572 return mainLen;
1573}

1575static void WriteEndMarker(CLzmaEnc *p, UInt32 posState)
1576{
1577 UInt32 len;
1578 RangeEnc_EncodeBit(&p->rc, &p->isMatch[p->state][posState], 1);
1579 RangeEnc_EncodeBit(&p->rc, &p->isRep[p->state], 0);
1580 p->state = kMatchNextStates[p->state];
1581 len = LZMA_MATCH_LEN_MIN;
1582 LenEnc_Encode2(&p->lenEnc, &p->rc, len - LZMA_MATCH_LEN_MIN, posState, !p->fastMode, p->ProbPrices);
1583 RcTree_Encode(&p->rc, p->posSlotEncoder[GetLenToPosState(len)], kNumPosSlotBits, (1 << kNumPosSlotBits) - 1);
1584 RangeEnc_EncodeDirectBits(&p->rc, (((UInt32) 1 << 30) - 1) >> kNumAlignBits, 30 - kNumAlignBits);
1585 RcTree_ReverseEncode(&p->rc, p->posAlignEncoder, kNumAlignBits, kAlignMask);
1586}

1620static void FillDistancesPrices(CLzmaEnc *p)
1621{
1622 UInt32 tempPrices[kNumFullDistances];
1623 UInt32 i, lenToPosState;
1624 for (i = kStartPosModelIndex; i < kNumFullDistances; i++)
1625 {
1626 UInt32 posSlot = GetPosSlot1(i);
1627 UInt32 footerBits = ((posSlot >> 1) - 1);
1628 UInt32 base = ((2 | (posSlot & 1)) << footerBits);
1629 tempPrices[i] = RcTree_ReverseGetPrice(p->posEncoders + base - posSlot - 1, footerBits, i - base, p->ProbPrices);
1630 }
1631
1632 for (lenToPosState = 0; lenToPosState < kNumLenToPosStates; lenToPosState++)
1633 {
1634 UInt32 posSlot;
1635 const CLzmaProb *encoder = p->posSlotEncoder[lenToPosState];
1636 UInt32 *posSlotPrices = p->posSlotPrices[lenToPosState];
1637 for (posSlot = 0; posSlot < p->distTableSize; posSlot++)
1638 posSlotPrices[posSlot] = RcTree_GetPrice(encoder, kNumPosSlotBits, posSlot, p->ProbPrices);
1639 for (posSlot = kEndPosModelIndex; posSlot < p->distTableSize; posSlot++)
1640 posSlotPrices[posSlot] += ((((posSlot >> 1) - 1) - kNumAlignBits) << kNumBitPriceShiftBits);
1641
1642 {
1643 UInt32 *distancesPrices = p->distancesPrices[lenToPosState];
1644 UInt32 i;
1645 for (i = 0; i < kStartPosModelIndex; i++)
1646 distancesPrices[i] = posSlotPrices[i];
1647 for (; i < kNumFullDistances; i++)
1648 distancesPrices[i] = posSlotPrices[GetPosSlot1(i)] + tempPrices[i];
1649 }
1650 }
1651 p->matchPriceCount = 0;
1652}

1711static SRes LzmaEnc_CodeOneBlock(CLzmaEnc *p, Bool useLimits, UInt32 maxPackSize, UInt32 maxUnpackSize)
1712{
1713 UInt32 nowPos32, startPos32;
1714 if (p->needInit)
1715 {
1716 p->matchFinder.Init(p->matchFinderObj);
1717 p->needInit = 0;
1718 }
1719
1720 if (p->finished)
1721 return p->result;
1722 RINOK(CheckErrors(p));
1723
1724 nowPos32 = (UInt32) p->nowPos64;
1725 startPos32 = nowPos32;
1726
1727 if (p->nowPos64 == 0)
1728 {
1729 UInt32 numPairs;
1730 Byte curByte;
1731 if (p->matchFinder.GetNumAvailableBytes(p->matchFinderObj) == 0)
1732 return Flush(p, nowPos32);
1733 ReadMatchDistances(p, &numPairs);
1734 RangeEnc_EncodeBit(&p->rc, &p->isMatch[p->state][0], 0);
1735 p->state = kLiteralNextStates[p->state];
1736 curByte = p->matchFinder.GetIndexByte(p->matchFinderObj, 0 - p->additionalOffset);
1737 LitEnc_Encode(&p->rc, p->litProbs, curByte);
1738 p->additionalOffset--;
1739 nowPos32++;
1740 }
1741
1742 if (p->matchFinder.GetNumAvailableBytes(p->matchFinderObj) != 0)
1743 for (;;)
1744 {
1745 UInt32 pos, len, posState;
1746
1747 if (p->fastMode)
1748 len = GetOptimumFast(p, &pos);
1749 else
1750 len = GetOptimum(p, nowPos32, &pos);
1751
1752#ifdef SHOW_STAT2
1753 printf("\n pos = %4X, len = %d pos = %d", nowPos32, len, pos);
1754#endif
1755
1756 posState = nowPos32 & p->pbMask;
1757 if (len == 1 && pos == (UInt32) -1)
1758 {
1759 Byte curByte;
1760 CLzmaProb *probs;
1761 const Byte *data;
1762
1763 RangeEnc_EncodeBit(&p->rc, &p->isMatch[p->state][posState], 0);
1764 data = p->matchFinder.GetPointerToCurrentPos(p->matchFinderObj) - p->additionalOffset;
1765 curByte = *data;
1766 probs = LIT_PROBS(nowPos32, *(data - 1));
1767 if (IsCharState(p->state))
1768 LitEnc_Encode(&p->rc, probs, curByte);
1769 else
1770 LitEnc_EncodeMatched(&p->rc, probs, curByte, *(data - p->reps[0] - 1));
1771 p->state = kLiteralNextStates[p->state];
1772 }
1773 else
1774 {
1775 RangeEnc_EncodeBit(&p->rc, &p->isMatch[p->state][posState], 1);
1776 if (pos < LZMA_NUM_REPS)
1777 {
1778 RangeEnc_EncodeBit(&p->rc, &p->isRep[p->state], 1);
1779 if (pos == 0)
1780 {
1781 RangeEnc_EncodeBit(&p->rc, &p->isRepG0[p->state], 0);
1782 RangeEnc_EncodeBit(&p->rc, &p->isRep0Long[p->state][posState], ((len == 1) ? 0 : 1));
1783 }
1784 else
1785 {
1786 UInt32 distance = p->reps[pos];
1787 RangeEnc_EncodeBit(&p->rc, &p->isRepG0[p->state], 1);
1788 if (pos == 1)
1789 RangeEnc_EncodeBit(&p->rc, &p->isRepG1[p->state], 0);
1790 else
1791 {
1792 RangeEnc_EncodeBit(&p->rc, &p->isRepG1[p->state], 1);
1793 RangeEnc_EncodeBit(&p->rc, &p->isRepG2[p->state], pos - 2);
1794 if (pos == 3)
1795 p->reps[3] = p->reps[2];
1796 p->reps[2] = p->reps[1];
1797 }
1798 p->reps[1] = p->reps[0];
1799 p->reps[0] = distance;
1800 }
1801 if (len == 1)
1802 p->state = kShortRepNextStates[p->state];
1803 else
1804 {
1805 LenEnc_Encode2(&p->repLenEnc, &p->rc, len - LZMA_MATCH_LEN_MIN, posState, !p->fastMode, p->ProbPrices);
1806 p->state = kRepNextStates[p->state];
1807 }
1808 }
1809 else
1810 {
1811 UInt32 posSlot;
1812 RangeEnc_EncodeBit(&p->rc, &p->isRep[p->state], 0);
1813 p->state = kMatchNextStates[p->state];
1814 LenEnc_Encode2(&p->lenEnc, &p->rc, len - LZMA_MATCH_LEN_MIN, posState, !p->fastMode, p->ProbPrices);
1815 pos -= LZMA_NUM_REPS;
1816 GetPosSlot(pos, posSlot);
1817 RcTree_Encode(&p->rc, p->posSlotEncoder[GetLenToPosState(len)], kNumPosSlotBits, posSlot);
1818
1819 if (posSlot >= kStartPosModelIndex)
1820 {
1821 UInt32 footerBits = ((posSlot >> 1) - 1);
1822 UInt32 base = ((2 | (posSlot & 1)) << footerBits);
1823 UInt32 posReduced = pos - base;
1824
1825 if (posSlot < kEndPosModelIndex)
1826 RcTree_ReverseEncode(&p->rc, p->posEncoders + base - posSlot - 1, footerBits, posReduced);
1827 else
1828 {
1829 RangeEnc_EncodeDirectBits(&p->rc, posReduced >> kNumAlignBits, footerBits - kNumAlignBits);
1830 RcTree_ReverseEncode(&p->rc, p->posAlignEncoder, kNumAlignBits, posReduced & kAlignMask);
1831 p->alignPriceCount++;
1832 }
1833 }
1834 p->reps[3] = p->reps[2];
1835 p->reps[2] = p->reps[1];
1836 p->reps[1] = p->reps[0];
1837 p->reps[0] = pos;
1838 p->matchPriceCount++;
1839 }
1840 }
1841 p->additionalOffset -= len;
1842 nowPos32 += len;
1843 if (p->additionalOffset == 0)
1844 {
1845 UInt32 processed;
1846 if (!p->fastMode)
1847 {
1848 if (p->matchPriceCount >= (1 << 7))
1849 FillDistancesPrices(p);
1850 if (p->alignPriceCount >= kAlignTableSize)
1851 FillAlignPrices(p);
1852 }
1853 if (p->matchFinder.GetNumAvailableBytes(p->matchFinderObj) == 0)
1854 break;
1855 processed = nowPos32 - startPos32;
1856 if (useLimits)
1857 {
1858 if (processed + kNumOpts + 300 >= maxUnpackSize || RangeEnc_GetProcessed(&p->rc) + kNumOpts * 2 >= maxPackSize)
1859 break;
1860 }
1861 else if (processed >= (1 << 15))
1862 {
1863 p->nowPos64 += nowPos32 - startPos32;
1864 return CheckErrors(p);
1865 }
1866 }
1867 }
1868 p->nowPos64 += nowPos32 - startPos32;
1869 return Flush(p, nowPos32);
1870}

1872#define kBigHashDicLimit ((UInt32)1 << 24)
1873
1874static SRes LzmaEnc_Alloc(CLzmaEnc *p, UInt32 keepWindowSize, ISzAlloc *alloc, ISzAlloc *allocBig)
1875{
1876 UInt32 beforeSize = kNumOpts;
1877 Bool btMode;
1878 if (!RangeEnc_Alloc(&p->rc, alloc))
1879 return SZ_ERROR_MEM;
1880 btMode = (p->matchFinderBase.btMode != 0);
1881#ifndef _7ZIP_ST
1882 p->mtMode = (p->multiThread && !p->fastMode && btMode);
1883#endif
1884
1885 {
1886 unsigned lclp = p->lc + p->lp;
1887 if (p->litProbs == 0 || p->saveState.litProbs == 0 || p->lclp != lclp)
1888 {
1889 LzmaEnc_FreeLits(p, alloc);
1890 p->litProbs = (CLzmaProb *) alloc->Alloc(alloc, (0x300 << lclp) * sizeof(CLzmaProb));
1891 p->saveState.litProbs = (CLzmaProb *) alloc->Alloc(alloc, (0x300 << lclp) * sizeof(CLzmaProb));
1892 if (p->litProbs == 0 || p->saveState.litProbs == 0)
1893 {
1894 LzmaEnc_FreeLits(p, alloc);
1895 return SZ_ERROR_MEM;
1896 }
1897 p->lclp = lclp;
1898 }
1899 }
1900
1901 p->matchFinderBase.bigHash = (p->dictSize > kBigHashDicLimit);
1902
1903 if (beforeSize + p->dictSize < keepWindowSize)
1904 beforeSize = keepWindowSize - p->dictSize;
1905
1906#ifndef _7ZIP_ST
1907 if (p->mtMode)
1908 {
1909 RINOK(MatchFinderMt_Create(&p->matchFinderMt, p->dictSize, beforeSize, p->numFastBytes, LZMA_MATCH_LEN_MAX, allocBig));
1910 p->matchFinderObj = &p->matchFinderMt;
1911 MatchFinderMt_CreateVTable(&p->matchFinderMt, &p->matchFinder);
1912 }
1913 else
1914#endif
1915 {

1924void LzmaEnc_Init(CLzmaEnc *p)
1925{
1926 UInt32 i;
1927 p->state = 0;
1928 for (i = 0; i < LZMA_NUM_REPS; i++)
1929 p->reps[i] = 0;
1930
1931 RangeEnc_Init(&p->rc);
1932
1933 for (i = 0; i < kNumStates; i++)
1934 {
1935 UInt32 j;
1936 for (j = 0; j < LZMA_NUM_PB_STATES_MAX; j++)
1937 {
1938 p->isMatch[i][j] = kProbInitValue;
1939 p->isRep0Long[i][j] = kProbInitValue;
1940 }
1941 p->isRep[i] = kProbInitValue;
1942 p->isRepG0[i] = kProbInitValue;
1943 p->isRepG1[i] = kProbInitValue;
1944 p->isRepG2[i] = kProbInitValue;
1945 }
1946
1947 {
1948 UInt32 num = 0x300 << (p->lp + p->lc);
1949 for (i = 0; i < num; i++)
1950 p->litProbs[i] = kProbInitValue;
1951 }
1952
1953 {
1954 for (i = 0; i < kNumLenToPosStates; i++)
1955 {
1956 CLzmaProb *probs = p->posSlotEncoder[i];
1957 UInt32 j;
1958 for (j = 0; j < (1 << kNumPosSlotBits); j++)
1959 probs[j] = kProbInitValue;
1960 }
1961 }
1962 {
1963 for (i = 0; i < kNumFullDistances - kEndPosModelIndex; i++)
1964 p->posEncoders[i] = kProbInitValue;
1965 }
1966
1967 LenEnc_Init(&p->lenEnc.p);
1968 LenEnc_Init(&p->repLenEnc.p);
1969
1970 for (i = 0; i < (1 << kNumAlignBits); i++)
1971 p->posAlignEncoder[i] = kProbInitValue;
1972
1973 p->optimumEndIndex = 0;
1974 p->optimumCurrentIndex = 0;
1975 p->additionalOffset = 0;
1976
1977 p->pbMask = (1 << p->pb) - 1;
1978 p->lpMask = (1 << p->lp) - 1;
1979}

2064{
2065 CSeqOutStreamBuf *p = (CSeqOutStreamBuf *) pp;
